#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn55.30"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.30:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.30:0.2"
msgid "3. Saraṇānivagga "
msgstr "3. About Sarakāni "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 30. Nandakalicchavisutta → nandakasuttaṃ (bj) | licchavi or nandaka (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.30:0.3"
msgid "30. Nandakalicchavisutta "
msgstr "30. With Nandaka the Licchavi "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn55.30:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof. "

msgctxt "sn55.30:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho nandako licchavimahāmatto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho nandakaṃ licchavimahāmattaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Nandaka the Licchavi minister went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.390, sc2
msgctxt "sn55.30:2.1"
msgid "“Catūhi kho, nandaka, dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo. "
msgstr "“Nandaka, a noble disciple who has four things is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening. "

msgctxt "sn55.30:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn55.30:2.3"
msgid "Idha, nandaka, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.30:2.4"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.30:2.5"
msgid "Dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.30:2.6"
msgid "saṅghe … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.30:2.7"
msgid "ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi. "
msgstr "And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion. "

msgctxt "sn55.30:2.8"
msgid "Imehi kho, nandaka, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo. "
msgstr "A noble disciple who has these four things is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening. "

# NOTE: Unusual use of samyutta is not noted in dict. Here it means “bound” as in “bound for” i.e. “guaranteed”.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn55.30:3.1"
msgid "Imehi ca pana, nandaka, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato ariyasāvako āyunā saṃyutto hoti dibbenapi mānusenapi; "
msgstr "A noble disciple who has these four things is guaranteed long life, "

msgctxt "sn55.30:3.2"
msgid "vaṇṇena saṃyutto hoti dibbenapi mānusenapi; "
msgstr "beauty, "

msgctxt "sn55.30:3.3"
msgid "sukhena saṃyutto hoti dibbenapi mānusenapi; "
msgstr "happiness, "

msgctxt "sn55.30:3.4"
msgid "yasena saṃyutto hoti dibbenapi mānusenapi; "
msgstr "fame, "

msgctxt "sn55.30:3.5"
msgid "ādhipateyyena saṃyutto hoti dibbenapi mānusenapi. "
msgstr "and sovereignty, both human and divine. "

msgctxt "sn55.30:3.6"
msgid "Taṃ kho panāhaṃ, nandaka, nāññassa samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā sutvā vadāmi. Api ca yadeva mayā sāmaṃ ñātaṃ sāmaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sāmaṃ viditaṃ, tadevāhaṃ vadāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Now, I don’t say this because I’ve heard it from some other ascetic or brahmin. I only say it because I’ve known, seen, and realized it for myself.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn55.30:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro puriso nandakaṃ licchavimahāmattaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, a certain person said to Nandaka: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.30:4.2"
msgid "“nahānakālo, bhante”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, it is time to bathe.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.30:4.3"
msgid "“Alaṃ dāni, bhaṇe, etena bāhirena nahānena. "
msgstr "“Enough now, my man, with that exterior bath. "

msgctxt "sn55.30:4.4"
msgid "Alamidaṃ ajjhattaṃ nahānaṃ bhavissati, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr "This interior bathing will do for me, that is, "

msgctxt "sn55.30:4.5"
msgid "bhagavati pasādo”ti. "
msgstr "confidence in the Buddha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.30:4.6"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.30:4.7"
msgid "Saraṇānivaggo tatiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn55.30:5.1"
msgid "Mahānāmena dve vuttā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.30:5.2"
msgid "godhā ca saraṇā duve; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.30:5.3"
msgid "Duve anāthapiṇḍikā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.30:5.4"
msgid "duve verabhayena ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.30:5.5"
msgid "Licchavī dasamo vutto, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.30:5.6"
msgid "vaggo tena pavuccatīti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
